-- Egypt Discussing Five-Year Loan for $1.3 Billion From World Bank
-- B y   A b d e l   L a t i f   W a h b a
-- 2010-11-04T13:31:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/egypt-discussing-five-year-loan-for-1-3-billion-from-world-bank.html
Egypt and the World Bank are
discussing a plan for $1.3 billion worth of loans to the North
African country between 2011 and 2015, International Cooperation
Minister  Fayza Aboulnaga  told reporters in Cairo today.  “There is a partnership strategy between Egypt and the
World Bank to finance some projects in energy, agriculture,
health, irrigation and education,” Aboulnaga said. “The amount
is $1.3 billion.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Abdel Latif Wahba  in Cairo at 
 alatifwahba@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Mahmoud Kassem at   mkassem1@bloomberg.net . 